text: Khamyshki () is a rural locality (a selo) in Dakhovskoye Rural Settlement of Maykopsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 297 as of 2018. There are 22 streets. == Geography == The village is located in the valley of the Belaya River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Maykopsky District
title: Khamyshki
